      • getTopLevelElementTypes

        protected abstract TokenSet getTopLevelElementTypes()
        Returns:
        All element types which don't have a parent, e.g. IF_STATEMENT. getDirectChildrenElementTypes(com.intellij.psi.tree.IElementType) should never return these element types

      • getKeywordElementTypes

        protected abstract TokenSet getKeywordElementTypes()
        Returns:
        Elements which should be highlighted. These elements don't have children. getDirectChildrenElementTypes(com.intellij.psi.tree.IElementType) should return an empty TokenSet for an element type if it is a keyword.

      • getBlockElementTypes

        protected abstract TokenSet getBlockElementTypes()
        Returns:

      • getDirectChildrenElementTypes

        protected abstract TokenSet getDirectChildrenElementTypes(IElementType parentElementType)
        The method defines a highlighting tree. Highlighting tree nodes are PSI elements. A highlighting tree has an edge from A to B if and only if
        • A is a parent for B in the PSI tree
        • getDirectChildrenElementTypes(getElementType(A)).contains(getElementType(B))
        If two keyword elements have a common ancestor in a highlighting tree they will be highlighted together. The method should be consistent with getTopLevelElementTypes() and getKeywordElementTypes().

        For example, for the given if statement: 

         if expr
 elsif expr
 else
 end
        the children should be defined as follows: 
         IF_STATEMENT => {kIF, ELSIF_BLOCK, ELSE_BLOCK, kEND}
 ELSIF_BLOCK => {kELSEIF}
 ELSE_BLOCK => {kELSE}

      • getCodeBlockMarkerRanges

        public java.util.List<TextRange> getCodeBlockMarkerRanges(PsiElement elementAtCursor)
        Description copied from interface: CodeBlockSupportHandler
        Checks if code block marker (or keyword) is under cursor and collects related markers: e.g. finds if/elsif/else if cursor is on the else from this compound statement.
        Specified by:
        getCodeBlockMarkerRanges in interface CodeBlockSupportHandler
        Returns:
        List of ranges of related structural markers or empty list if there is no structural marker under cursor or it should not be handled (highlighted) for any reason.
